sections.History:
===[[Season 1]]===
Silent Sisters dress and prepare the bodies of Lord [[Jon Arryn]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming (episode)|Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; and, later, Ser [[Hugh]] of [[the Vale]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; for burial. They perform a complex funeral ceremony for Jon Arryn, involving marching in a circle around his body as it lies in state while carrying vessels filled with burning incense, and periodically turning to bow towards the body.

===[[Season 2]]===
Silent Sisters are seen tending the wounded as [[Robb Stark]] surveys the field in the aftermath of the [[Battle of Oxcross]]. A pair of Silent Sisters deliver a box containing [[Eddard Stark|Ned Stark]]'s bones to [[Catelyn Stark]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Garden of Bones]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===

The [[Red Priest]]ess [[Melisandre]], devoted to the religion of the [[R'hllor|Lord of Light]], mocks the Silent Sisters for taking vows of celibacy when she meets with [[Gendry]] on [[Dragonstone]]. Given that Red Priestesses do not take vows of celibacy, she then proceeds to seduce Gendry.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Second Sons (episode)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Silent Sisters stand vigil for the body of King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] along with the [[High Septon]] and other [[septon]]s at the [[Great Sept of Baelor]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Breaker of Chains]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
